Here's a summary of the key breaking changes and required migrations for each item:

---

### 1. `WebHostBuilder` → `WebApplication.CreateBuilder()`
The legacy `WebHost.CreateDefaultBuilder()` hosting model is **removed** in .NET 10. Migrate to the minimal hosting model:

```csharp
// Before (.NET 9)
var host = WebHost.CreateDefaultBuilder(args)
    .UseStartup<Startup>()
    .Build();

// After (.NET 10)
var builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);
// move Startup.ConfigureServices → inline here
var app = builder.Build();
// move Startup.Configure → inline here
app.Run();
```

---

### 2. `.WithOpenApi()` removed
The `WithOpenApi()` extension on minimal API endpoints is **removed**. Use **operation transformers** with `AddOpenApi()` instead:

```csharp
// Before
app.MapGet("/items", () => …).WithOpenApi();

// After — enrich via transformers
builder.Services.AddOpenApi(options =>
{
    options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
    {
        // customise the OpenApiOperation here
        return Task.CompletedTask;
    });
});
app.MapOpenApi();          // serves the doc at /openapi/v1.json
```

---

### 3. `<IncludeOpenApiAnalyzers>` removed
This MSBuild property is **no longer recognised**. Remove it from your `.csproj`. The relevant analyzers now ship in-box with the `Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi` package.

```xml
<!-- Remove this line -->
<IncludeOpenApiAnalyzers>true</IncludeOpenApiAnalyzers>
```

---

### 4. `Microsoft.Extensions.ApiDescription.Client` (NSwag codegen)
This package still functions, but the server-side doc generation it consumes has changed. Make sure your build-time OpenAPI doc is now produced by the new `MapOpenApi()` pipeline (backed by `Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi`). If you were relying on Swashbuckle to emit the doc at build time, you'll need to switch to the built-in provider or run the app and fetch `/openapi/v1.json` for client generation.

---

### 5. `IActionContextAccessor` as singleton
The default `ActionContextAccessor` implementation uses `AsyncLocal`, so it historically **worked** as a singleton. In .NET 10, **scope-validation is stricter by default** — the DI container will warn or throw when a scoped-dependent service is captured in a singleton. Register it as **scoped** instead:

```csharp
// Before
builder.Services.AddSingleton<IActionContextAccessor, ActionContextAccessor>();

// After
builder.Services.AddHttpContextAccessor(); // if not already
builder.Services.AddScoped<IActionContextAccessor, ActionContextAccessor>();
```

---

### 6. `IPNetwork` type replaced
`Microsoft.AspNetCore.HttpOverrides.IPNetwork` is **removed**. Use the BCL type `System.Net.IPNetwork` (available since .NET 8):

```csharp
// Before
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.HttpOverrides;
options.KnownNetworks.Add(new IPNetwork(IPAddress.Parse("10.0.0.0"), 8));

// After
using System.Net;
options.KnownNetworks.Add(new IPNetwork(IPAddress.Parse("10.0.0.0"), 8));
```

The constructor signature is the same, so usually just the `using` changes.

---

### 7. `AddRazorRuntimeCompilation()` removed
The `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Razor.RuntimeCompilation` package **no longer ships for .NET 10**. Remove the NuGet reference and the call:

```csharp
// Remove
builder.Services.AddRazorPages().AddRazorRuntimeCompilation();
```

**Replacement:** Use `dotnet watch` for hot-reload during development. It recompiles Razor views/pages automatically on save.

---

### 8. 401 → login-page redirect
In .NET 10, cookie authentication **no longer redirects API requests to a login page** by default. Requests with `Accept: application/json` (or those hitting API endpoints) get a bare **401** status. If you had a workaround like a custom `OnRedirectToLogin` handler, you can likely remove it. If you **want** the old redirect behavior, explicitly configure it:

```csharp
builder.Services.AddAuthentication().AddCookie(options =>
{
    options.Events.OnRedirectToLogin = ctx =>
    {
        ctx.Response.Redirect(ctx.RedirectUri); // keep old behavior
        return Task.CompletedTask;
    };
});
```

---

### Quick checklist

| Area | Action |
|---|---|
| Hosting model | Replace `WebHostBuilder` / `Startup` with `WebApplication.CreateBuilder` |
| `.WithOpenApi()` | Delete; use `AddOpenApi()` + transformers |
| `IncludeOpenApiAnalyzers` | Remove from csproj |
| NSwag codegen | Point at `/openapi/v1.json` from `MapOpenApi()` |
| `IActionContextAccessor` | Change to scoped registration |
| `IPNetwork` | Switch using to `System.Net` |
| Razor runtime compilation | Remove package & call; use `dotnet watch` |
| 401 redirect | Remove custom workarounds; bare 401 is now the default for APIs |
